    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="181"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d181">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/234½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State of a Conversation with
                        the Nicaraguan Minister</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Chamorro</hi>), <hi
                        rend="italic">August 3, 1922</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1922-08-03">August 3, 1922</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The Minister of Nicaragua called attention to the memorandum from the Secretary,
                    under date of October 27, 1921,<note n="80" xml:id="d181fn80">
                        <ref target="frus1921v01#pg_235">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 235</ref>.</note> referring to the
                    boundary dispute with Honduras and suggesting that there should be an
                    arbitration by the Chief Justice of the United States. The Minister said that
                    Nicaragua had accepted the proposal and inquired as to the attitude of Honduras.
                    The Secretary informed him that Honduras had not yet accepted. The Minister
                    asked whether Honduras could not be again approached. The Secretary said he
                    would review the correspondence and see what could be done in the matter.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
            </div>
